# Results ::: {.cell} ::: *Note: All fishing effort and capture results are current as of 2023-11-09.* ## Fish capture During fieldwork in summers 2021 - 2023: - Over course of 62 fieldwork days 2021 - 2023 (including the training event), we conducted a total of 108 sampling events at 82 unique sites. See the interactive project map in the Methods section ("[Site selection](##%20Site%20selection)") for a current map of where and when sampling events have occurred. \[MAP WILL BE UPDATED FOR 2023\] - Table @tbl-sites summarises total sampling events by individual site. ## AWC Nominations Fish capture data was evaluated against the 2021 and 2022 Anadromous Waters Catalog to identify new stream segment nominations. Complete submission materials may be accessed in the project [Google Drive folder (link)](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1UmQGruxbmRO-ICCd0xbGi5rPp1ZTFCX2?usp=drive_link). Nominations were sent to the ADF&G Habitat Division in Anchorage in the fall of each year. ::: {.callout-note appearance="simple"} ## Total Anadromous Waters Nominations As of November 2023, a total length of **17.5 miles** of stream segments and **1152 lake acres** were included in the nominations. ::: Table @tbl-awc-noms below breaks down each stream segment nomination by length. ::: {#tbl-awc-noms .cell tbl-cap='Lengths of stream segments included in anadromous waters nominations.'} ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}

For general background on nominations, see the [slides linked here](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1uQX9_4T-vJDzp_gzBJFyqtggOg1Fpsng?rtpof=true&usp=drive_fs), presented at Kenai Watershed Forum's Fireside Chat series held at Kenai River Brewing on November 1, 2023. ## Volunteer participation Volunteer recruitment efforts resulted in a steadily increasing level of participation from the general public. A total of 310 volunteer hours were documented throughout the project, with an initial higher outlay in 2021 to initiate training.
::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](results_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: The level of volunteer participation, along with experience gained, closely tracked the quantity of nominations submitted each year, with a steadily rising number of nominations from 2021 to 2023.
s ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](results_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-8-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: ## Aquatic Resource Permit Fish capture data was reformatted each fall in to a csv file for submission to ADF&G in fulfillment of the required [Aquatic Resource Permit](http://www.adfg.alaska.gov/index.cfm?adfg=otherlicense.aquatic_reports)[^results-1]; available in the online in [this project's GitHub repo](https://github.com/Kenai-Watershed-Forum/tu_awc_expansion/tree/main/output)[^results-2].
